{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PonAeiQu5NceZBvGqbs1CE","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have now read all the requested files. Let me provide you with a complete summary of the file contents:\n\n---\n\n## File 1: /root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/daemon.rs\n\n**Full Contents:**\n\nThis file (234 lines) defines the CLI interface for daemon operations with the following components:\n\n- **DaemonCommand struct** with subcommands: Start, Status, Abort, Retry, Reconcile\n- **handle function** - main entry point that dispatches to appropriate handlers\n- **handle_start** - Initializes stores (filesystem, worktree, projects, snapshots, journals, artifacts, amendments) and runs the daemon loop with configurable polling interval\n- **handle_status** - Lists daemon tasks showing task_id, status, lease_id, heartbeat, and issue reference\n- **handle_abort** - Transitions a claimed/active task to aborted and cleans up its lease\n- **handle_retry** - Returns a failed task to pending status and increments attempt count\n- **handle_reconcile** - Reconciles stale daemon state, releasing orphaned leases and failing stale tasks\n- **cleanup_aborted_task** - Helper that waits for daemon cleanup with grace period before releasing leases\n\n---\n\n## File 2: /root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs\n\n**Full Contents:** (5517 lines total)\n\nThis massive conformance test file registers executable scenario tests across multiple domains:\n\n### Test Infrastructure:\n- **TempWorkspace** - Temporary directory management with auto-cleanup\n- **CLI helpers** - run_cli, run_cli_with_env, binary_path\n- **Assertion helpers** - assert_success, assert_failure, assert_contains, assert_not_contains\n- **File readers** - read_journal, read_run_snapshot, count_payload_files, count_artifact_files\n- **Workspace setup** - init_workspace, create_project_fixture,