{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017FZspHYJjDVsFcd9xjCR68","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see — the daemon_loop.rs uses concrete `AgentExecutionService<A, R, S>` generics that match the CLI's stub backend. The requirements service needs an `AgentExecutionService<A, R, S>` where A, R, S match. So `self.agent_service` should work since it has the same types. But `RequirementsService::new` takes ownership of an `AgentExecutionService`, not a reference.\n\nThe simplest approach: create a dedicated function that builds both the agent service and requirements service like the CLI does, and call it from within the daemon_loop methods. Let me update the requirements dispatch methods to do this:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":991,"cache_read_input_tokens":128436,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":991},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8dacb19c-9278-40df-b484-c803ec7bbb98","uuid":"6d0a7e56-a3ff-46e5-ba01-3f5f4a245383"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017FZspHYJjDVsFcd9xjCR68","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019zN1Fym7qxsYNgeGXGTNhH","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs","old_string":"    /// Handle requirements_quick dispatch: invoke requirements quick, link the\n    /// run ID to the task, derive seed, create project, then continue through\n    /// workflow execution in the same cycle.\n    async fn handle_requirements_quick(\n        &self,\n        base_dir: &Path,\n        task: &DaemonTask,\n    ) -> AppResult<()> {\n        let req_store = self.requirements_store.ok_or_else(|| {\n            AppError::RequirementsHandoffFailed {\n                task_id: task.task_id.clone(),\n                details: \"no requirements store configured for daemon\".to_owned(),\n            }\n        })?;\n\n        // Claim into active state for requirements work (no worktree needed yet)\n        let mut current = self.store.read_task(base_dir, &task.task_id)?;\n\n        // Use the agent service to run requirements quick\n        let req_svc = crate::contexts::requirements_drafting::service::RequirementsService::new(\n            self.agent_service.clone_with_defaults(),\n            crate::adapters::fs::FsRequirementsStore,\n        );\n\n        let idea = task.prompt.clone().unwrap_or_else(|| {\n            format!(\"Automated task for issue {}\", task.issue_ref)\n        });\n\n        let run_id = match req_svc.quick(base_dir, &idea, Utc::now()).await {\n            Ok(run_id) => run_id,\n            Err(e) => {\n                let _ = DaemonTaskService::mark_failed(\n                    self.store,\n                    base_dir,\n                    &task.task_id,\n                    \"requirements_quick_failed\",\n                    &e.to_string(),\n                );\n                return Err(e);\n            }\n        };\n\n        // Link requirements run to task\n        current = self.store.read_task(base_dir, &task.task_id)?;\n        current.requirements_run_id = Some(run_id.clone());\n        current.updated_at = Utc::now();\n        self.store.write_task(base_dir, &current)?;\n\n        DaemonTaskService::append_journal_event(\n            self.store,\n            base_dir,\n            super::model::DaemonJournalEventType::RequirementsHandoff,\n            json!({\n                \"task_id\": task.task_id,\n                \"requirements_run_id\": run_id,\n                \"dispatch_mode\": \"requirements_quick\",\n            }),\n        )?;\n\n        // Derive seed and create project from completed requirements run\n        let handoff = match req_service::extract_seed_handoff(req_store, base_dir, &run_id) {\n            Ok(h) => h,\n            Err(e) => {\n                let _ = DaemonTaskService::mark_failed(\n                    self.store,\n                    base_dir,\n                    &task.task_id,\n                    \"seed_handoff_failed\",\n                    &e.to_string(),\n                );\n                return Err(e);\n            }\n        };\n\n        // Use routed flow, not the seed's recommended flow (routed flow is authoritative)\n        let routed_flow = task.resolved_flow.unwrap_or(handoff.flow);\n        if handoff.flow != routed_flow {\n            println!(\n                \"daemon: seed suggests flow '{}' but routed flow '{}' is authoritative\",\n                handoff.flow.as_str(),\n                routed_flow.as_str()\n            );\n        }\n\n        // Update task to workflow mode for continuation\n        let mut updated = self.store.read_task(base_dir, &task.task_id)?;\n        updated.dispatch_mode = DispatchMode::Workflow;\n        updated.project_id = handoff.project_id.clone();\n        updated.project_name = Some(handoff.project_name.clone());\n        updated.prompt = Some(handoff.prompt_body.clone());\n        self.store.write_task(base_dir, &updated)?;\n\n        // Mark task completed — the seed and requirements are done.\n        // The project can be started separately via the normal workflow path.\n        let _ = DaemonTaskService::mark_completed(self.store, base_dir, &task.task_id);\n        println!(\n            \"daemon: requirements_quick completed for task '{}', run_id='{}'\",\n            task.task_id, run_id\n        );\n\n        Ok(())\n    }\n\n    /// Handle requirements_draft dispatch: invoke requirements draft to generate\n    /// questions, then transition to WaitingForRequirements state.\n    async fn handle_requirements_draft(\n        &self,\n        base_dir: &Path,\n        task: &DaemonTask,\n    ) -> AppResult<()> {\n        let _req_store = self.requirements_store.ok_or_else(|| {\n            AppError::RequirementsHandoffFailed {\n                task_id: task.task_id.clone(),\n                details: \"no requirements store configured for daemon\".to_owned(),\n            }\n        })?;\n\n        let req_svc = crate::contexts::requirements_drafting::service::RequirementsService::new(\n            self.agent_service.clone_with_defaults(),\n            crate::adapters::fs::FsRequirementsStore,\n        );\n\n        let idea = task.prompt.clone().unwrap_or_else(|| {\n            format!(\"Automated task for issue {}\", task.issue_ref)\n        });\n\n        let run_id = match req_svc.draft(base_dir, &idea, Utc::now()).await {\n            Ok(run_id) => run_id,\n            Err(e) => {\n                let _ = DaemonTaskService::mark_failed(\n                    self.store,\n                    base_dir,\n                    &task.task_id,\n                    \"requirements_draft_failed\",\n                    &e.to_string(),\n                );\n                return Err(e);\n            }\n        };\n\n        // Transition to waiting state — release all resources\n        match DaemonTaskService::mark_waiting_for_requirements(\n            self.store,\n            base_dir,\n            &task.task_id,\n            &run_id,\n        ) {\n            Ok(_) => {\n                DaemonTaskService::append_journal_event(\n                    self.store,\n                    base_dir,\n                    super::model::DaemonJournalEventType::RequirementsHandoff,\n                    json!({\n                        \"task_id\": task.task_id,\n                        \"requirements_run_id\": run_id,\n                        \"dispatch_mode\": \"requirements_draft\",\n                    }),\n                )?;\n                println!(\n                    \"daemon: requirements_draft started for task '{}', waiting for answers (run_id='{}')\",\n                    task.task_id, run_id\n                );\n            }\n            Err(e) => {\n                // Requirements run is still addressable via `requirements show`\n                let _ = DaemonTaskService::mark_failed(\n                    self.store,\n                    base_dir,\n                    &task.task_id,\n                    \"requirements_linking_failed\",\n                    &e.to_string(),\n                );\n                return Err(e);\n            }\n        }\n\n        Ok(())\n    }","new_string":"    /// Handle requirements_quick dispatch: invoke requirements quick, link the\n    /// run ID to the task, derive seed, create project, then continue through\n    /// workflow execution in the same cycle.\n    async fn handle_requirements_quick(\n        &self,\n        base_dir: &Path,\n        task: &DaemonTask,\n    ) -> AppResult<()> {\n        let req_store = self.requirements_store.ok_or_else(|| {\n            AppError::RequirementsHandoffFailed {\n                task_id: task.task_id.clone(),\n                details: \"no requirements store configured for daemon\".to_owned(),\n            }\n        })?;\n\n        let idea = task.prompt.clone().unwrap_or_else(|| {\n        