{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user is a software developer implementing a feature specification for \"Daemon Issue Watchers and Requirements Handoff\" (Loop 16) in the `ralph-burning-rewrite` Rust project. The spec requires:\n   - Adding a watcher/ingestion port to `automation_runtime` that polls external issue candidates\n   - Idempotent watched issue ingestion with `issue_ref`, `source_revision`, resolved flow, and dispatch mode\n   - Requirements commands: `/rb requirements draft` (interactive) and `/rb requirements quick` (one-shot seed)\n   - `requirements_quick` tasks invoke drafting to completion, persist `requirements_run_id`, then continue through workflow\n   - `requirements_draft` tasks invoke drafting, persist linked run, transition to `WaitingForRequirements` state\n   - State invariants: waiting tasks hold no writer lock, no worktree lease, no active workflow run\n   - Resume logic: when `requirements answer` completes, next daemon cycle resumes the waiting task\n   - Failure invariants around requirements run linking, seed generation, and project creation\n   - Routed flow precedence over seed-recommended flow\n   - Conformance coverage and fixing stale `SC-PROJ-009` fixture\n   - Updated `daemon status` output\n   \n   The output format must be a markdown implementation notes file (first implementation pass).\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - Rust monolith with bounded contexts (ports/adapters architecture)\n   - Daemon task lifecycle with state machine: Pending → Claimed → Active → Completed/Failed/Aborted, plus new WaitingForRequirements state\n   - Idempotent ingestion keyed on (issue_ref, source_revision) pair\n   - Dispatch modes: Workflow, RequirementsDraft, RequirementsQuick\n   - Requirements drafting service with draft/quick/show/answer commands\n   - Worktree leases and writer locks for daemon tasks\n   - Conformance testing via scenario registry with Gherkin feature files\n   - serde JSON serialization with backward compatibility (default values)\n   - Nix-based development environment for building/testing\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **`src/contexts/automation_runtime/model.rs`** (REWRITTEN)\n     - Core model file for daemon automation. Added `DispatchMode` enum, `WatchedIssueMeta` struct, three new fields to `DaemonTask`, `WaitingForRequirements` variant to `TaskStatus`, and new journal event types.\n     - Key additions:\n     ```rust\n     #[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\n     #[serde(rename_all = \"snake_case\")]\n     pub enum DispatchMode {\n         Workflow,\n         RequirementsDraft,\n         RequirementsQuick,\n     }\n     \n     #[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\n     pub struct WatchedIssueMeta {\n         pub issue_ref: String,\n         pub source_revision: String,\n         pub title: String,\n         pub body: String,\n         pub labels: Vec<String>,\n         #[serde(default, skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\")]\n         pub routing_command: Option<String>,\n     }\n     ```\n     - New DaemonTask fields: `dispatch_mode: DispatchMode` (with `default_dispatch_mode` for backward compat), `source_revision: Option<String>`, `requirements_run_id: Option<String>`\n     - TaskStatus now includes `WaitingForRequirements` with transitions: Active→WaitingForRequirements, WaitingForRequirements→Pending/Failed/Aborted\n     - New DaemonJournalEventType variants: WatcherIngestion, RequirementsHandoff, RequirementsWaiting, RequirementsResumed\n\n   - **`src/contexts/automation_runtime/watcher.rs`** (NEW FILE)\n     - Defines `IssueWatcherPort` trait, `parse_requirements_command`, `resolve_dispatch_mode`, `resolve_watched_issue_flow`\n     ```rust\n     pub trait IssueWatcherPort {\n         fn poll(&self, base_dir: &Path) -> AppResult<Vec<WatchedIssueMeta>>;\n     }\n     \n     pub fn parse_requirements_command(text: &str) -> AppResult<Option<DispatchMode>> {\n         // Parses /rb requirements draft|quick from text, multiline-aware\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **`src/adapters/issue_watcher.rs`** (NEW FILE)\n     - `FileIssueWatcher` reads from `.ralph-burning/daemon/watched/*.json`\n     - `InMemoryIssueWatcher` for testing with fixed candidates\n\n   - **`src/adapters/mod.rs`** (MODIFIED)\n     - Added `pub mod issue_watcher;`\n\n   - **`src/contexts/automation_runtime/mod.rs`** (MODIFIED)\n     - Added `pub mod watcher;` and updated exports to include `DispatchMode, WatchedIssueMeta, IssueWatcherPort`\n\n   - **`src/shared/error.rs`** (MODIFIED)\n     - Added three new error variants:\n     ```rust\n     WatcherIngestionFailed { issue_ref: String, details: String },\n     RequirementsHandoffFailed { task_id: String, details: String },\n     DuplicateWatchedIssue { issue_ref: String, source_revision: String },\n     ```\n\n   - **`src/contexts/automation_runtime/task_service.rs`** (MODIFIED)\n     - Added `dispatch_mode` and `source_revision` to `CreateTaskInput`\n     - Added `dispatch_mode`, `source_revision`, `requirements_run_id` to task construction in `create_task`\n     - Added three new methods:\n       - `create_task_from_watched_issue` - idempotent ingestion by (issue_ref, source_revision), generates task_id from issue_ref+revision\n       - `mark_waiting_for_requirements` - transitions Active→WaitingForRequirements, sets requirements_run_id, clears lease\n       - `resume_from_waiting` - transitions WaitingForRequirements→Pending, switches dispatch_mode to Workflow\n\n   - **`src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs`** (MODIFIED)\n     - Added daemon-facing helpers after the service impl block:\n     ```rust\n     pub fn read_requirements_run_status(store, base_dir, run_id) -> AppResult<RequirementsRun>\n     pub fn is_requirements_run_complete(store, base_dir, run_id) -> AppResult<bool>\n     pub fn extract_seed_handoff(store, base_dir, run_id) -> AppResult<SeedHandoff>\n     \n     pub struct SeedHandoff {\n         pub project_id: String,\n         pub project_name: String,\n         pub flow: FlowPreset,\n         pub prompt_body: String,\n         pub prompt_path: PathBuf,\n         pub recommended_flow: Option<FlowPreset>,\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **`src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs`** (REWRITTEN)\n     - Added `watcher: Option<&'a dyn IssueWatcherPort>` and `requirements_store: Option<&'a dyn RequirementsStorePort>` fields\n     - Added `with_watcher` and `with_requirements_store` builder methods\n     - `process_cycle` now calls `poll_watchers()` then `check_waiting_tasks()` before processing pending tasks\n     - `process_task` branches on `dispatch_mode`: RequirementsQuick→`handle_requirements_quick`, RequirementsDraft→`handle_requirements_draft`, Workflow→standard path\n     - `handle_requirements_quick`: builds fresh RequirementsService, runs quick, links run_id, extracts seed handoff, enforces routed flow over seed flow, marks completed\n     - `handle_requirements_draft`: builds RequirementsService, runs draft, transitions to WaitingForRequirements\n     - `check_waiting_tasks`: iterates waiting tasks, checks if linked requirements run is complete, resumes if so\n     - `build_requirements_service` helper function creates a standalone RequirementsService with StubBackendAdapter (same pattern as CLI)\n\n   - **`src/cli/daemon.rs`** (MODIFIED)\n     - Added imports for `FileIssueWatcher` and `FsRequirementsStore`\n     - Wired `.with_watcher(&issue_watcher).with_requirements_store(&requirements_store)` into daemon loop construction\n     - Updated status output format to include `dispatch={}` and `requirements_run={}`\n\n   - **`src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs`** (MODIFIED)\n     - Fixed SC-PROJ-009: added `stage_cursor` to the run.json fixture:\n     ```rust\n     let run_json = r#\"{\"active_run\":{\"run_id\":\"run-1\",\"stage_cursor\":{\"stage\":\"planning\",\"cycle\":1,\"attempt\":1,\"completion_round\":1},\"started_at\":\"2026-03-11T19:00:00Z\"},...}\"#;\n     ```\n     - Added `register_daemon_issue_intake` function with 8 scenarios (DAEMON-INTAKE-001 through 008)\n     - Registered in `build_registry`\n\n   - **`tests/conformance/features/daemon_issue_intake.feature`** (NEW FILE)\n     - 8 Gherkin scenarios covering watcher ingestion, idempotent re-polling, requirements quick/draft handoff, duplicate rejection, routed flow override, unknown command failure, status output\n\n   - **`tests/unit/automation_runtime_test.rs`** (REWRITTEN)\n     - Updated `sample_task()` to include new fields (dispatch_mode, source_revision, requirements_run_id)\n     - Added tests: task_state_machine_active_to_waiting, waiting_to_pending/failed/aborted, watched_issue_ingestion_creates_task_idempotently, watched_issue_newer_revision_after_terminal_creates_fresh_task (FAILING), watched_issue_different_revision_while_non_terminal_fails, waiting_for_requirements_resume_transitions, resume_from_non_waiting_state_fails, parse_requirements_command tests (5), dispatch_mode_display, JSON roundtrip test, backward compat deserialization test\n\n   - **`tests/unit/requirements_drafting_test.rs`** (MODIFIED)\n     - Added `daemon_handoff` module with 3 tests: is_requirements_run_complete_returns_false_for_drafting, returns_true_for_completed, read_requirements_run_status_returns_run\n\n   - **`tests/cli.rs`** (MODIFIED)\n     - Added `DispatchMode` import\n     - Added `dispatch_mode: DispatchMode::Workflow, source_revision: None, requirements_run_id: None` to all 8 existing DaemonTask literals via sed\n     - Added 3 new E2E tests: daemon_status_shows_waiting_for_requirements_task, daemon_status_shows_dispatch_mode, daemon_abort_waiting_task_succeeds\n\n4. Errors and Fixes:\n   - **`cargo` not found**: PATH wasn't s