{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Dmiop4p7UZMdvEBkyi2ZmV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Feature: Daemon Issue Watchers and Requirements Handoff\n     2→  The daemon polls external issue sources, creates tasks through routing rules,\n     3→  and dispatches into workflow execution or requirements handoff paths.\n     4→\n     5→  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-001 - Watcher ingestion creates task from watched issue\n     6→    Given a workspace is initialized\n     7→    And a watched issue file exists with issue_ref \"test/repo#1\" and source_revision \"abc12345\"\n     8→    When the daemon polls for new issues\n     9→    Then a pending task is created for issue_ref \"test/repo#1\"\n    10→    And the task has source_revision \"abc12345\"\n    11→    And the task dispatch_mode is \"workflow\"\n    12→\n    13→  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-002 - Idempotent re-polling skips existing issue\n    14→    Given a workspace is initialized\n    15→    And a task already exists for issue_ref \"test/repo#1\" with source_revision \"abc12345\"\n    16→    When the watcher returns the same issue_ref and source_revision\n    17→    Then no new task is created\n    18→    And the existing task remains unchanged\n    19→\n    20→  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-003 - Requirements quick handoff completes in one cycle\n    21→    Given a workspace is initialized\n    22→    And a watched issue with \"/rb requirements quick\" command\n    23→    When the daemon processes the task\n    24→    Then the requirements run completes with a seed\n    25→    And the task is linked to the requirements_run_id\n    26→    And the task transitions to completed\n    27→\n    28→  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-004 - Requirements draft enters waiting state\n    29→    Given a workspace is initialized\n    30→    And a watched issue with \"/rb requirements draft\" command\n    31→    When the daemon processes the task\n    32→    Then the requirements run creates a question set\n    33→    And the task transitions to waiting_for_requirements\n    34→    And the task holds no lease, no writer lock, and no active workflow run\n    35→\n    36→  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-005 - Duplicate issue with different revision rejected\n    37→    Given a workspace is initialized\n    38→    And a non-terminal task exists for issue_ref \"test/repo#2\"\n    39→    When the watcher returns issue_ref \"test/repo#2\" with a different source_revision\n    40→    Then the ingestion fails with DuplicateWatchedIssue\n    41→    And no new task is created\n    42→\n    43→  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-006 - Routed flow overrides seed recommendation\n    44→    Given a workspace is initialized\n    45→    And a watched issue with routing command \"/rb flow quick_dev\"\n    46→    And the completed seed recommends flow \"standard\"\n    47→    When the daemon creates the project from the seed\n    48→    Then the project uses flow \"quick_dev\" (the routed flow)\n    49→    And a warning is recorded about the flow override\n    50→\n    51→  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-007 - Unknown requirements command fails ingestion\n    52→    Given a workspace is initialized\n    53→    And a watched issue body contains \"/rb requirements unknown\"\n    54→    When the watcher attempts to ingest the issue\n    55→    Then ingestion fails with WatcherIngestionFailed\n    56→    And no task is created\n    57→\n    58→  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-008 - Daemon status surfaces waiting state\n    59→    Given a workspace is initialized\n    60→    And a task exists in waiting_for_requirements with requirements_run_id \"req-123\"\n    61→    When \"daemon status\" is run\n    62→    Then the output includes \"waiting_for_requirements\"\n    63→    And the output includes \"requirements_run=req-123\"\n    64→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8dacb19c-9278-40df-b484-c803ec7bbb98","uuid":"e422ce7a-61b2-4468-b018-71e282fe7652","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/daemon_issue_intake.feature","content":"Feature: Daemon Issue Watchers and Requirements Handoff\n  The daemon polls external issue sources, creates tasks through routing rules,\n  and dispatches into workflow execution or requirements handoff paths.\n\n  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-001 - Watcher ingestion creates task from watched issue\n    Given a workspace is initialized\n    And a watched issue file exists with issue_ref \"test/repo#1\" and source_revision \"abc12345\"\n    When the daemon polls for new issues\n    Then a pending task is created for issue_ref \"test/repo#1\"\n    And the task has source_revision \"abc12345\"\n    And the task dispatch_mode is \"workflow\"\n\n  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-002 - Idempotent re-polling skips existing issue\n    Given a workspace is initialized\n    And a task already exists for issue_ref \"test/repo#1\" with source_revision \"abc12345\"\n    When the watcher returns the same issue_ref and source_revision\n    Then no new task is created\n    And the existing task remains unchanged\n\n  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-003 - Requirements quick handoff completes in one cycle\n    Given a workspace is initialized\n    And a watched issue with \"/rb requirements quick\" command\n    When the daemon processes the task\n    Then the requirements run completes with a seed\n    And the task is linked to the requirements_run_id\n    And the task transitions to completed\n\n  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-004 - Requirements draft enters waiting state\n    Given a workspace is initialized\n    And a watched issue with \"/rb requirements draft\" command\n    When the daemon processes the task\n    Then the requirements run creates a question set\n    And the task transitions to waiting_for_requirements\n    And the task holds no lease, no writer lock, and no active workflow run\n\n  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-005 - Duplicate issue with different revision rejected\n    Given a workspace is initialized\n    And a non-terminal task exists for issue_ref \"test/repo#2\"\n    When the watcher returns issue_ref \"test/repo#2\" with a different source_revision\n    Then the ingestion fails with DuplicateWatchedIssue\n    And no new task is created\n\n  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-006 - Routed flow overrides seed recommendation\n    Given a workspace is initialized\n    And a watched issue with routing command \"/rb flow quick_dev\"\n    And the completed seed recommends flow \"standard\"\n    When the daemon creates the project from the seed\n    Then the project uses flow \"quick_dev\" (the routed flow)\n    And a warning is recorded about the flow override\n\n  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-007 - Unknown requirements command fails ingestion\n    Given a workspace is initialized\n    And a watched issue body contains \"/rb requirements unknown\"\n    When the watcher attempts to ingest the issue\n    Then ingestion fails with WatcherIngestionFailed\n    And no task is created\n\n  Scenario: DAEMON-INTAKE-008 - Daemon status surfaces waiting state\n    Given a workspace is initialized\n    And a task exists in waiting_for_requirements with requirements_run_id \"req-123\"\n    When \"daemon status\" is run\n    Then the output includes \"waiting_for_requirements\"\n    And the output includes \"requirements_run=req-123\"\n","numLines":64,"startLine":1,"totalLines":64}}}
