{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UYHa2TxNxg3QjYkXjuSJVz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Feature: Daemon Lifecycle Commands\n     2→  The daemon foreground loop processes pending tasks, exposes status, and\n     3→  supports abort and retry transitions for terminal recovery flows.\n     4→\n     5→  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-001\n     6→  Scenario: Daemon start processes one pending task in a single iteration\n     7→    Given a git-backed workspace with a pending daemon task\n     8→    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon start --single-iteration\"\n     9→    Then the daemon claims the task\n    10→    And the daemon rebases the task worktree onto the default branch\n    11→    And the task finishes in a terminal status\n    12→    And the task lease is released\n    13→\n    14→  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-002\n    15→  Scenario: Daemon status lists non-terminal tasks first\n    16→    Given daemon tasks exist in statuses \"pending\", \"active\", and \"completed\"\n    17→    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon status\"\n    18→    Then the non-terminal tasks appear before the completed task\n    19→    And each row includes lease and heartbeat data when present\n    20→\n    21→  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-003\n    22→  Scenario: Abort transitions a claimed task to aborted and cleans up its lease\n    23→    Given a claimed daemon task with a persisted lease\n    24→    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon abort <task-id>\"\n    25→    Then the task transitions to \"aborted\"\n    26→    And the worktree lease is released\n    27→    And the task worktree is removed\n    28→\n    29→  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-004\n    30→  Scenario: Retry returns a failed task to pending"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8dacb19c-9278-40df-b484-c803ec7bbb98","uuid":"8f1001c1-4d6a-407e-9ebb-0c589b94bb38","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/daemon_lifecycle.feature","content":"Feature: Daemon Lifecycle Commands\n  The daemon foreground loop processes pending tasks, exposes status, and\n  supports abort and retry transitions for terminal recovery flows.\n\n  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-001\n  Scenario: Daemon start processes one pending task in a single iteration\n    Given a git-backed workspace with a pending daemon task\n    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon start --single-iteration\"\n    Then the daemon claims the task\n    And the daemon rebases the task worktree onto the default branch\n    And the task finishes in a terminal status\n    And the task lease is released\n\n  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-002\n  Scenario: Daemon status lists non-terminal tasks first\n    Given daemon tasks exist in statuses \"pending\", \"active\", and \"completed\"\n    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon status\"\n    Then the non-terminal tasks appear before the completed task\n    And each row includes lease and heartbeat data when present\n\n  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-003\n  Scenario: Abort transitions a claimed task to aborted and cleans up its lease\n    Given a claimed daemon task with a persisted lease\n    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon abort <task-id>\"\n    Then the task transitions to \"aborted\"\n    And the worktree lease is released\n    And the task worktree is removed\n\n  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-004\n  Scenario: Retry returns a failed task to pending","numLines":30,"startLine":1,"totalLines":41}}}
